 HONEYCOMB Confectioneries Limited has rolled out the drums in celebration of its fifth anniversary in a series of events that includes a thanksgiving service, Distributors’ Forum, and the first annual guest lecture tagged: “Eating Right, Eating Healthy in the State of Pandemic.” The Executive Vice Chairperson of the company, Biyi Tunji-Olugbodi, said the lecture, which is slated for Wednesday, November 25, 2020, as a virtual conference, is the first of its kind from the organisation and the theme is a reflection of the new world order that warrants eating healthy. She said, “As part of our Corporate Social Responsibility, we have decided to put together this event so that we can educate the public on a topical issue such as this. The world has become hybrid and human activities have reduced, however, everyone needs to know the best way of nourishing their bodies.” The keynote Speaker of the virtual event is Dr. Joy Odimegwu of the Department of Pharmacognosy, the College of Medicine, University of Lagos. Others are the Special Guests of Honour: Lola Akande, the Lagos State Commissioner for Commerce, Industry, and Cooperatives, and Abisola Olusanya, the Commissioner for Agriculture.